  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 10.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The valley of Zephathah at Mareshah",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". \"At\" some translate \"belonging to,\" some more suitably to the exact connection \"near.\" The Hebrew here for\" valley\" is ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "גֵיא",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". It can scarcely designate necessarily a \"ravine.\" It is a valley in the sense of being a low, fiat region, in which springs of water \"broke out.\" From ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 21:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", the first occasion of its occurrence, to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Zechariah 14:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " it is found fifty-six times, and is always rendered (Authorized Version) \"valley;\" it is the word used in the celebrated passages, \"Though I walk through the valley\" etc. (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 23:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); and \"Every valley shall be exalted\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 40:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The Septuagint, however, do not render it uniformly; but though they render it generally ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "φάραξ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", they also have ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ναπή κοίλας αὐλών",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and in some cases the simple word ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "γῆ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "e.g.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἐν γῇ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "γε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "Ἑννόμ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 28:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 33:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), which, nevertheless, elsewhere they describe as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "φάραξ Ἑννόμ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 15:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The full explanation may probably be that the word is used for the valley that narrowed up to a ravine-like pass, or gorge, or that opened out into one of the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "wide wadies",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of the country; but see Stanley's 'Sinai and Palestine,' Appendix, pp. 482, 483, new edit., 1866. It is supposed that Zephathah is not mentioned elsewhere, but see the Zephath of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 1:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; and comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 21:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 30:30",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which Keil and Bertheau think conclusively to be not the same. 2 Chronicles 14:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
